column4: The seeker loves comedies and documentaries, especially comedies. They enjoy watching movies both in theaters and at home, and frequently use Netflix. They particularly like dumb and ridiculous comedies, similar to 'This Is The End'. They are a fan of the first two Austin Powers movies, but disliked the third. They also enjoy Rowan Atkinson and Mr. Bean, appreciating his chaotic but innocent energy.

column4: The seeker is open to any movie genre and can find something to enjoy in most films. They appreciate both good acting/script and high production value. They enjoy Coen Brothers films from 2000 onward and like monster or slasher horror movies but dislike ghost/paranormal horror. They appreciate creative horror movies like 'It Follows' and 'You're Next', and enjoyed 'Hereditary' and 'Midsommar'. They think A24 and Blumhouse tend to put out quality films.

They tend to get annoyed if movies try to push too hard on a political agenda.

They enjoy movies like The Thing, Texas Chainsaw Massacre, Fright Night, Goodfellas, and Platoon, and recently enjoyed Joker and Doctor Sleep. They've seen the original Japanese and American remake versions of The Ring and enjoy Sam Elliott, particularly in The Big Lebowski. They have also seen Paranormal Activity and don't mind hand-held or shaky cam movies. They like ghost movies, citing The Shining as fantastic and are looking for recommendations in that sub-genre. They also enjoy psychological horror films like Silence of the Lambs and are looking for more recent ghost or psychological horror recommendations.

He/she has seen the Spiderman movies with Toby McGuire and is planning on watching the rest of the Avengers movies to see how Spiderman affects them. He/she is interested in the Black Widow character.

They don't mind dirty jokes in the interest of comedy, but prefer to watch such movies after their kids have gone to bed. They enjoy stories with sidelines.

column4: The seeker is interested in romantic comedies, especially those that are hilarious and relatable. She enjoyed Bridesmaids. She also liked Always Be My Maybe because the main actors were Asian American, and she is interested in seeing more diverse casts and more movies with Asian American actors.

They prefer Joaquin Phoenix's portrayal of the Joker over Heath Ledger's, finding Phoenix's version darker and more deranged. They dislike superhero movies, finding them predictable and repetitive. They did not enjoy Suicide Squad due to disliking the actors and overall theme.

The seeker likes to rewatch movies to catch details they missed initially or to gain a new perspective knowing the ending. They have watched all the Marvel movies in chronological order and enjoyed them. They appreciate a good balance of humor and story, as well as great music and a fantastic cast.

column4: The seeker is a huge fan of horror films, especially those that focus on dread rather than gore. They enjoyed 'A Quiet Place' for its unique reliance on silence but prefers a more traditional film that isn't entirely silent, while still maintaining a sense of dread. They appreciate fresh takes on genres and are open to slower-paced, thoughtful horror movies without excessive jump scares. They also prefer movies with lesser-known actors, finding it easier to relate to the characters when they aren't distracted by the actor's fame.

They found the comedy in Venom funny despite it being a miss for many people and are interested in good chemistry between characters.
